RACE.RACE_TEXT: OLD DOMINION HOUNDS RACE 1 2M Hurdle CR: N/A. Maiden Special Weight Purse 25000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES FOR MAIDENS FILLIES AND MARES, FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Four-year- olds, 145 lbs.; older, 153 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FITS THE JILL raced close up throughout, was sent to lead narrowly two hurdles out, dueled to the wire and was up in time for the win. DREAM NORTH led from the start, was headed two hurdles out, dueled to the wire and just missed. RIGHT TEMPO (FR) raced close up throughout, contended two hurdles out, held by top two finishers. FOX FORCE FIVE tracked the leaders on inside path, then weakened two hurdles out. TANKA TOUGH was hard held from start traveling in second for the first circuit, then dropped back when about a half mile to go. FOX IN THE PARK (IRE) was never a threat. AFRAID NOT rated towards the rear and was never a threat. LACEY UNDERALL showed little. HIPNOTIZADA trailed and was pulled up.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: OLD DOMINION HOUNDS RACE 2 2M Hurdle CR: N/A. Maiden Special Weight Purse 25000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES FOR MAIDENS, FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Four-year-olds, 146 lbs.; older, 154 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HOFFMAN (IRE) led boldly, was twelve lengths clear about a half mile out, clearly in command throughout and hand ridden out to the wire . RIENDO closed well for second but no match for the winner. HIGH DEFF (FR) rated, stayed on for a late gain. REWIND (GB) gave an even effort, never being a threat. MYSTICAL MAN was held up towards the rear, finished evenly never being a threat. KEYS DISCOUNT stalked the pacesetter in second, faded three hurdles out, pulled up before two out. BY THE RIVERSIDE (FR) tired and was pulled up. BE YOURSELF showed no speed, trailed the pack and was pulled up. THALEEQ (GB) unseated the rider early in the race.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: OLD DOMINION HOUNDS RACE 3 3M Timber CR: N/A. Allowance Purse 15000. FOR FIVE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Five-year-olds, 165 lbs.; older, 170 lbs. Non-winners of a timber stakes, allowed 5 lbs.; of a race over timber, 10 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STOOSHIE (IRE) was reserved in the rear, ridden to head leader two fences out, dueled to wire and prevailed driving. STORM TEAM set pace most of race, was headed two fences out, dueled to the wire and just missed. NATHANIELHAWTHORNE (GB) settled tracking in third, closed strongly between horses in the stretch. RAKHAA (GB) tracked the pacesetter in second, led briefly mid race, weakened slightly yet stayed on.
